            "language": "eng",
            "description": "This dataset contains genotypic and phenotypic data used to investigate the genomic architecture of drought adaptation in white spruce (Picea glauca), a widely distributed North American conifer. It includes gene SNP genotypes (6153 SNPs), phenotypes related to anatomy, growth response and climate-sensitivity, as well as environmental data for 1473 trees sampled in 43 natural populations from the province of Quebec. Trees were planted in a common garden established in 1979 in Mastigouche (Québec, Canada).",
